This directory contains third-party assets vendored into pidgin and
redistributed under the MIT License, plus two hand-written faithful shims of
named exports from the pi project.

Vendored asset:
  typebox-1.1.38.mjs
    upstream:  typebox (npm), version 1.1.38
    homepage:  https://github.com/sinclairzx81/typebox
    author:    Haydn Paterson (sinclair)

How it was produced:
  typebox 1.1.38's root export (its package "." entry, ./build/index.mjs) is a
  multi-file ES-module graph (~690 .mjs files). It was bundled into this single,
  self-contained ESM file with esbuild 0.28.1:

    npx esbuild build/index.mjs --bundle --format=esm --platform=neutral \
      --outfile=typebox-1.1.38.mjs

  Bundling to one file (no internal relative imports left to resolve) lets
  pidgin's extension module loader serve typebox as a single asset. The named
  export `Type` (and `Type.Object(...)`) is preserved; verified in Node before
  vendoring. A first-line straitjacket-allow-file marker was prepended so the
  bundled machine-generated JS does not trip the repo's source linters; the
  bundle body is otherwise the unmodified esbuild output.

  The asset is served by pidgin's deno extension module loader
  (crates/pidgin-extensions/src/module_loader.rs) for the bare specifiers
  `typebox` and `@sinclair/typebox`, mirroring pi's jiti virtualModules alias.

Faithful shims of pi named exports:
  pi-ai-shim.mjs
  pi-coding-agent-shim.mjs
  pi-tui-shim.mjs
    upstream: pi (earendil-works/pi), MIT License, Copyright (c) 2025 Mario Zechner
    homepage: https://github.com/earendil-works/pi

  These two files are hand-written, behavior-faithful shims of the extension-
  facing VALUE exports of pi's `@earendil-works/pi-ai` and
  `@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent` packages, so that real upstream `defineTool`
  tool extensions load, register, and invoke on pidgin's deno plane. They are
  adaptations rather than verbatim copies:

    pi-ai-shim.mjs mirrors pi's packages/ai/src/index.ts extension VALUE surface
    (`export { Type } from "typebox"`) plus `StringEnum`, whose body is copied
    faithfully from packages/ai/src/utils/typebox-helpers.ts (TS generics and the
    `as any` cast are erased at transpile, so the runtime body is identical). The
    nested `typebox` import resolves through the same loader to the vendored
    TypeBox bundle above, sharing `Type`'s identity.

    pi-coding-agent-shim.mjs mirrors pi's `defineTool`
    (packages/coding-agent/src/core/extensions/types.ts:497), which is a pure
    identity function; the shim is the equivalent `(tool) => tool`.

    pi-tui-shim.mjs is a RENDER-STUB shim of `@earendil-works/pi-tui`
    (packages/tui/src/index.ts). The UI component classes it exports — Text, Box,
    Container, Spacer, Markdown (packages/tui/src/components/*.ts and tui.ts) — are
    touched by an extension ONLY in its display hooks (renderResult / renderCall),
    which pidgin's HEADLESS plane never calls (invoke runs the tool's `execute`
    only; the inventory records metadata alone). So the shim serves them as marker
    classes: the constructor stores its args and `render()` returns a
    `{ __piTuiStub }` marker. That is behavior-faithful for load / register /
    invoke; only display output changes, and the headless plane produces none. The
    shim also ports pi's pure `Key` const (packages/tui/src/keys.ts) to JS
    (its TypeScript generic parameters erase at transpile, leaving an identical
    runtime body). pi-tui utilities with heavy or host-coupled dependencies —
    `truncateToWidth` (imports the external `get-east-asian-width` package) and
    `matchesKey` (reads process.env) — are intentionally omitted: they are
    display / input-time code the headless plane never runs, and no vendored
    example imports them. First introduced alongside the vendored
    examples/extensions/structured-output/index.ts example (PR 242 line of work).

  The loader serves them for the bare specifiers `@earendil-works/pi-ai`,
  `@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent`, and `@earendil-works/pi-tui`, mirroring pi's
  jiti virtualModules alias. pi's MIT license (Copyright (c) 2025 Mario Zechner)
  governs these adaptations; its full text is reproduced in
  examples/extensions/NOTICE.

